params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.endpoint
params.description: Required. The name of the Endpoint resource from which to undeploy a Model. Format: projects/{project}/locations/{location}/endpoints/{endpoint}

params.name: data.deployed_model_id
params.description: Required. The ID of the DeployedModel to be undeployed from the Endpoint.

params.name: data.traffic_split
params.description: If this field is provided, then the Endpoint's [traffic_split][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Endpoint.traffic_split] will be overwritten with it. If last DeployedModel is being undeployed from the Endpoint, the [Endpoint.traffic_split] will always end up empty when this call returns. A DeployedModel will be successfully undeployed only if it doesn't have any traffic assigned to it when this method executes, or if this field unassigns any traffic to it.
